The World Health Organization halted two trials of vaginal microbicides due to safety concerns, but research on promising microbicides must continue to prevent HIV infections.
In South Africa, 22 women in a gel trial contracted HIV, prompting an investigation.
Male circumcision trials in Kenya and Uganda show a significant reduction in HIV risk, with potential to prevent thousands of infections.
Studies on treating herpes alongside HIV offer hope for controlling the virus.
Despite challenges, efforts to combat HIV/AIDS in Africa are ongoing, emphasizing the need for improved healthcare and prevention strategies.
